 </header>Commence in Closed or Contact Position

 | **Man** | **Foot Position** | **Alignment** | **Turn** | **Foot-    work** | **Lead &amp; Shape** | **Count** |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | [Appel](../technique/p_appel.md) on RF | Facing wall | No turn or slight body turn to L | WF | Commence PP Shape | 1 |
| 2 | LF to side in PP | Moving along LOD, facing DW | 1/8 to L between 1&amp;2 | HF | Achieve PP Shape | 2 |
| 3 | RF fwd in PP and CBMP | Facing DW | Commence to turn R | HF | Maintain PP Shape | 3 |
| 4 | LF side and slightly back | Backing LOD | 3/8 to R between 3&amp;4 | BF | Commence CPP Shape | 4 |
| 5 | RF back, R side leading | " | No turn | BF | Achieve CPP Shape | 5 |
| 6 | LF back in CBMP, Lady outside | Down LOD, toe turned in | Commence to turn R | BF | Maintain CPP Shape | 6 |
| 7 | Close RF to LF | Facing centre | 1/4 to R between 6&amp;7 | BF | Commence to move arms to R side | 7 |
| 8 | [Sur Place](sur_place.md) LF | " | Slight body turn to R | BF | Extend arms to R side and release hold with R hand, allowing it to gradually slide along Lady's L arm to end with double hand hold | 8 |
| 9-12 | Hold position with feet together | Facing centre | Gradually turn body to L | Feet flat | Move arms from R to L to lead Lady to L side. On 12, raise R arm and incline body to L. Circle hand anticlockwise | 1.2    3.4 |
| 13-16 | Hold position with feet together | " | Gradually turn body to R | Feet flat | Circle R arm anticlockwise over head and lower it to R side, slightly fwd, to lead Lady behind back and to R side. At same time, take L hand behind back at waist level. Gradually change inclination of body to R | 5.6    7.8 |
| 17-20 | Hold position with feet together | " | Gradually turn body to L | Feet flat | Reverse arm positions, taking L arm to L side, slightly fwd, to lead Lady behind back and to L side with R hand behind back at waist level. gradually change inclination of body to L | 1.2    3.4 |
| 21.22 | Hold position with feet together | " | Turn body to normal position | Feet flat | Release L to R hand hold and take R arm toward R side to lead Lady to circle behind back toward R side. Return body to normal position | 5.6 |
| 23 | LF back | Backing wall | No turn | BF | Extend R arm slightly fwd to lead Lady to pass on R side | 7 |
| 24 | Close RF to LF without weight | Facing centre | " | BF | Move R hand fwd in front of body to lead Lady to continue her circle | 8 |
| 25.26 | Hold position weight weight on LF | " | " | Feet flat | Move R hand very slightly to L, then take it down and to R to turn Lady to R, immediately releasing hold. Take L to R hold at end of Lady's turn with L arm in normal position | 1.2 |
| 27 | RF to side | " | " | B or BF | Return to normal hold over 27 and 28 | 3 |
| 28 | Close LF to RF | " | " | B or BF |  | 4 |

 | **Lady** | **Foot Position** | **Alignment** | **Turn** | **Footwork** | **Count** |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | [Appel](../technique/p_appel.md) on LF | Facing centre | No turn or slight body turn to R | WF | 1 |
| 2 | RF to side in PP | Moving along LOD, facing DC | 1/8 to R between 1&amp;2 | HF | 2 |
| 3 | LF fwd and across in PP and CBMP | Pointing LOD | 1/8 to R between 2&amp;3, body turns less | HF | 3 |
| 4 | RF fwd | Facing LOD | Body completes turn | HF | 4 |
| 5 | LF fwd, L side leading, preparing to step OP | " | No turn | HF | 5 |
| 6 | RF fwd in CBMP, OP | " | Commence to turn R | HF | 6 |
| 7 | LF to side and slightly back | Backing DC | 3/8 to R between 6&amp;7 | BF | 7 |
| 8 | RF back in line with LF at a 90° angle to Man on his R side, toe turned out. K knee flexed (Spanish Line) | Down LOD | 1/8 to R between 7&amp;8 | BF of RF, L heel high from floor | 8 |
| 9 | LF fwd | Facing against LOD | No turn | HF | 1 |
| 10 | RF fwd | " | " | HF | 2 |
| 11 | LF fwd | Facing DW against LOD | 1/8 to L between 10&amp;11 | BF | 3 |
| 12 | RF fwd toward Man's L side, then turn underarm on RF to end with LF crossed loosely in front without weight (Spiral turn) | Facing wall. End facing wall | 1/8 to L between 11&amp;12, then a complete turn | BF of RF. T of LF | 4 |
| 13 | LF fwd | Facing DW | 1/8 to L between 12&amp;13 | HF | 5 |
| 14 | RF fwd | " | Commence to turn R | HF | 6 |
| 15 | LF to side and slightly back | Backing centre | 1/8 to R between 14&amp;15 | BF | 7 |
| 16 | RF back and slightly across, OP on R side, toe turned out, L knee flexed (Spanish Line) | DC | 1/8 to R between 15&amp;16 | BF of RF of RF, L heel high from floor | 8 |
| 17 | LF fwd, toe turned out | DW against LOD | Commence to turn L | HF | 1 |
| 18 | RF to side and slightly back | Backing centre | 1/8 to L between 17&amp;18 | BF | 2 |
| 19 | LF back and slightly across, OP on L, toe turned out | DC against LOD | 1/8 to L between 18&amp;19 | BF | 3 |
| 20 | RF back in line with LF, toe turned out. L knee flexed (Spanish Line) | " | No turn | BF of RF, L heel high from floor | 4 |
| 21 | LF fwd, behind Man's back | Facing DW | Commence to turn L | HF | 5 |
| 22 | RF fwd, behind Man's back | Facing DC | 1/4 to L between 21&amp;22 | HF | 6 |
